I've lived in the neighborhood for years (10+), but never actually tried this place until a couple years ago, when my kitchen was being renovated and I was eating out for every meal. I can say the food has always been good. Not great or anything to write home about, but it's consistent and the portions are always more than enough for me. It always hits the spot and holds me for several hours. They do free coffee refills, which are always a great. The service used to be REALLY slow, but I've been twice in the past three weeks and that aspect has improved dramatically. The dining room is cute, looks and feels like you're literally in "ma n pops" eat-in kitchen, circa 1982. There's no bathroom for patrons, unfortunately, so just know that before you go to eat in. Otherwise, they do take orders for pickup. Since I live so close, I'm not sure if they do delivery through any of the apps out there.

Wish i could give them zero stars.  I use to order from here quite often, both directly and through seamless (not anymore).   I placed a $40.00 order.  The girl that brought it called and said food is outside.  Ask her to ring the bell 1st fl.  She said she cant come upstairs.  I said im on the 1st fl.  She says she a girl and cant come in the building. I said im in a wheelchair and cant come out the building, im right on the 1st fl. She sighs oh well.  So i say ill call seamless and my money back since she can't deliver my food, she hangs up.  Keep in mind, I've ordered from this restaurant more than 10 times in the last 3 yrs.  Never had any delivery person not bring my food to my 1st fl apt.  THEN, the restaurant refuses to give my money back, because she lied and said i didn't tell her I was in a wheelchair.  I than tried to call the restaurant to speak to the manager or someone in charge and this boy (yes boy, because he was unprofessional) tells me theirs no one there and he doesn't know when they come in.  I will definitely be letting everyone i know and recommended this restaurant to,  not to order from them anymore.  We'll be ordering from the soul food spot from now in.  If you don't deliver into a building than you should let customers know you only do curbside deliveries.

I've frequented this spot for quite a while now. Even gave rave reviews and encouraged others to patronize this black owned business. Last night I had a taste for their baked macaroni and CHEESE. I ordered a catfish dinner with A side of candies yams. I also ordered and extra side of mac n cheese as well as potatoe salad. I can't begin to say how disappointed I was. The fish NO SEASONING, the Mac n Cheese....No cheese. I mean it had a cheese flavor but there was little to NO CHEESE in a dish that I ALWAYS get and used to talk about. I thought maybe it was just my serving so as I served my children I seen theirs had no cheese either. The potatoe salad was blah as well. No seasons. I seen black pepper specks but no trace of salt. I think they may have even used sodium free mayo. I hope they get it together and go back to seasoning the food the way it's supposed to be seasoned. Or adding CHEESE to a dish that calls for CHEESE!
